2.00	King's_Troop	King's Troop, Royal Horse Artillery	The King's Troop, Royal Horse Artillery is a ceremonial unit of the British Army, quartered at Woolwich. It is a mounted unit and all of its soldiers are trained to care for and drive teams of six horses pulling each of six First World War-era 13-pounder state saluting guns. Its duties include the firing of royal salutes on royal anniversaries and state occasions, and providing a gun carriage and team of black horses for state and military funerals. The unit is most often seen providing gun salutes on state occasions in Hyde Park, and Green Park.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a6/Horseguardssentry.jpg/250px-Horseguardssentry.jpg
